snippet: They’re not expecting an unbiased investigation from the Republican-led committee, and are torn between lending it more legitimacy and letting it proceed unchecked.
abstract: House Democrats make it clear that they do not expect fair proceedings from Republican-led panel tasked with investigating 2012 attack in Benghazi, Libya, offering no definitive answer on whether they will appoint any of their own members to participate; party is torn between lending panel more legitimacy and letting it proceed unchecked.
lead_paragraph: They’re not expecting an unbiased investigation from the Republican-led committee, and are torn between lending it more legitimacy and letting it proceed unchecked.

headline.main: Democrats Look Dubiously at Joining Benghazi Panel
headline.print_headline: Democrats Look Dubiously at Joining Benghazi Panel
